of the sky.

A breeze reaches the pines, and I

Join in the general applause.

But we all know it cannot last,

The mountain is too weak to wait—

Even if reproduced and glassed

In me as in a paperweight.





Line 98: On Chapman’s Homer


A reference to the title of Keats’ famous sonnet (often quoted in America) which, owing to a printer’s absent-mindedness, has been drolly transposed, from some other article, into the account of a sports event. For other vivid misprints see note to li